  "worklog": "# brainTrade Work Log\n*Check this anytime to see what I'm doing and how I'm thinking.*\n\n## 2026-04-29 01:06 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 4] Fear & Greed only earns a small fear-side boost; the greed penalty is unproven and should come out\n\n**Task:** Re-test the Fear & Greed overlay against the full `data/03h-shadow-sim-results.csv` sample, check whether it still improves PM trade quality, and tighten the runtime mapping so it only reflects edges the data actually supports.\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive (`pm-bot`, `hl-bot`).\n- I matched all **1,168** shadow-sim trades to **20** daily Fear & Greed prints from Alternative.me.\n- The sample still does **not** contain any greed regime days; it is all fear/neutral, so our existing greed-side penalties were not backed by live sample evidence.\n- Across the full sample, day-level Fear & Greed had basically **no explanatory power** for WR on its own (**correlation -0.03**).\n- The usable signal is narrower: on the production-quality strong-bias subset (**|bias| >= 50**), WR was **87.4%** when F&G was **<= 25** versus **80.0%** in neutral conditions and **86.4%** overall.\n- Current live F&G is **26 (Fear)**, which sits just outside the only clearly supported boost zone.\n- I updated `polymarket-assistant/src/fear_greed.py` to remove the unproven greed penalties and shrink the overlay to a conservative asymmetric map: **+0.03 at <=15, +0.02 at 16-25, 0.00 above 25**, with matching mild size multipliers only in fear.\n- Verified the file with `py_compile` and a live script run; it now returns **0.00 / 1.00x** at today\u2019s F&G reading of **26**.\n\n**My thinking:** Fear & Greed is not a standalone regime engine for us; it is a light context feature. The data says it can help slightly when sentiment is washed out, but it does not justify pretending we know how PM behaves in greed when we have not traded enough of that regime. Carrying untested negative branches would just inject fake precision into sizing.\n\